  <main>
    <section>
      <div>
        <img src="images/ratatouille.png" alt="Confit Byaldi from Ratatouille" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>Confit Byaldi (Ratatouille, 2007)</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
        <p>A real French dish made famous in Pixar’s <em>Ratatouille</em>. Remy’s version turns this humble vegetable dish into culinary art.</p>
        <p>Beautifully layered, oven-roasted slices of eggplant, zucchini, and more over savory tomato sauce.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div>
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>1 eggplant</li>
          <li>1 zucchini</li>
          <li>1 yellow squash</li>
          <li>1 red bell pepper</li>
          <li>2 cups tomato sauce</li>
          <li>1 garlic clove</li>
          <li>Olive oil</li>
          <li>Salt</li>
          <li>Thyme</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).</li>
          <li>Thinly slice all vegetables into rounds.</li>
          <li>Spread tomato sauce mixed with minced garlic in a baking dish.</li>
          <li>Arrange the sliced vegetables in a spiral pattern on top.</li>
          <li>Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with thyme.</li>
          <li>Cover with parchment paper and bake for 45–50 minutes.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

